ree to plunge into the healing waters of action.” Featuring a new foreword by James biographer Michael Gorra as well as the original introductions by James and his good friend William Dean Howells, this long-forgotten perennial calendar will be an essential bibelot for James’s most ardent devotees and newest converts alike, a treasure to be cherished daily, across all seasons, for years, for ages to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aQuotations, American. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / General.2bisacsh  a"e of the day, calendar, victorian literature, british, american, classics, english major, novels, essays, travel, "es, "ations, excerpts, reviews, plays, henry james, famous authors, roderick hudson, isabel archer, washington square, wings dove, ambassadors, aspen papers, turn screw, haunting, possession, seasons, nature, observations, fiction, art, social commentary, observation.1 aGarnaut Smalley, Evelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorra, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorra, Michael.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226408682423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226408682/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles